Linux Checklist for hardening Cyberpatriot machines

To Do:
Finish section 3 - pam

1) Answer the Forensics questions

2) User Auditing
  a) Disable the guest account
    i) go to `/etc/lightdm/lightdm.conf`
    ii) add line `allow-guest=false`
    iii) save the file
  b) Make sure all admins are authorized to be admins
    i) double check this in `/etc/group` 
      ia) group sudo and admin
  c) Delete unauthorized users
    i) save their files

3) Password Auditing
  a) in `/etc/login.defs`
    i) change the lines:
      ```
      PASS_MIN_DAYS *
      PASS_MAX_DAYS *
      PASS_WARN_AGE *
      ```
      to
      ```
      PASS_MIN_DAYS 7
      PASS_MAX_DAYS 30
      PASS_WARN_AGE 14
      ```
    ii) PAM files
      iia) run `sudo apt install libpam-cracklib`
      iib) go to `/etc/pam.d/common-password`
        
        
4) Enable the firewall
  a) install ufw
    i) `sudo apt install ufw`
  b) enable firewall
    i) `sudo ufw enable`
  c) ensure no apps are runnning on the firewall
    i) `sudo ufw app list`

5) IPtables/ports - More to add
  run `iptables.sh`
 
 6) Look for unwanted software/malware
   a) MAKE SURE IT IS NOT A CRITICAL SERVICE
   b) run `wack.sh`



